name: listDockLocationsUsingGET
requestQuery:
[{
  "name" : "dockLocation",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Dock location which we are trying to find.\n",
  "required" : false,
  "type" : "string"
}, {
  "name" : "limit",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Maximum number of records that will be returned for this request.\n The default value is 50 records.\n",
  "required" : true,
  "type" : "integer",
  "format" : "int32",
  "x-example" : 0
}, {
  "name" : "locationStatus",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Dock location status.\nValid values are: \"NOT_SET\", \"EMPTY\", \"FULL\", \"INVENTORY_ERROR\", \"PARTIALLY_FULL\", \"LOCKED\", \"PENDING\".\n",
  "required" : false,
  "type" : "string"
}, {
  "name" : "offset",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Index of the first record returned for this request.\n",
  "required" : true,
  "type" : "integer",
  "format" : "int32",
  "x-example" : 0
}, {
  "name" : "transportEquipmentType",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Type of the transport equipment, which helps to limit the dock locations based on the type of transport equipment.\nValid values are: \"UNKNOWN_EQUIPMENT_TYPE\", \"STORAGE\", \"RECEIVING_EQUIPMENT_TYPE\", \"SHIPPING\".\n",
  "required" : false,
  "type" : "string"
}, {
  "name" : "warehouseId",
  "in" : "query",
  "description" : "Warehouse identifier.\n",
  "required" : true,
  "type" : "string"
}]
